[2026-03-13T19:18:43Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F81cnT9Hi7BVCZkVgug3tU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me create a detailed summary.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Go Project Architecture and Implementation\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the Cloche project. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n### 1. **Overall Directory Structure**\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── cmd/                          # Three binary entry points\n│   ├── cloche/                   # CLI client (short-lived)\n│   ├── cloched/                  # Daemon (long-running)\n│   └── cloche-agent/             # In-container agent\n├── internal/                      # Core domain logic\n│   ├── domain/                   # Types: Run, Workflow, RunState\n│   ├── ports/                    # Interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore)\n│   ├── adapters/                 # Implementations\n│   │   ├── docker/               # Docker runtime + image building/extraction\n│   │   ├── sqlite/               # SQLite store (runs, captures, logs, evolution)\n│   │   ├── grpc/                 # gRPC server\n│   │   ├── local/                # Local (non-container) runtime\n│   │   ├── web/                  # HTTP web dashboard\n│   │   └── agents/               # Agent adapters (prompt, generic)\n│   ├── config/                   # Configuration (TOML from ~/.config/cloche and .cloche/)\n│   ├── dsl/                      # Workflow DSL parser/lexer\n│   ├── agent/                    # Container-side agent runner\n│   ├── host/                     # Host workflow executor\n│   ├── evolution/                # Self-evolving tooling\n│   ├── logstream/                # Log broadcasting\n│   ├── protocol/                 # Status message types\n│   ├── runcontext/               # Context variables\n│   └── engine/                   # Execution engine\n├── api/                           # Protocol Buffers definitions\n│   ├── proto/cloche/v1/          # cloche.proto\n│   └── clochepb/                 # Generated gRPC code\n├── examples/                      # Example projects\n├── docker/                        # Docker image build artifacts\n├── docs/                          # User documentation\n├── test/                          # Integration tests\n├── go.mod / go.sum               # Module: github.com/cloche-dev/cloche\n└── Makefile                       # Build automation\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **CLI Setup (cloche/main.go)**\n\n**Module**: `github.com/cloche-dev/cloche`\n\n**gRPC Client Connection**:\n- Address: Env var `CLOCHE_ADDR` or default `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`\n- Credentials: Insecure (no TLS)\n- Timeout: 30 seconds for most operations\n- Connection: `grpc.NewClient()` with `insecure.NewCredentials()`\n\n**Commands (Daemon-Aware)**:\n- **No daemon needed**: `init`, `health`, `get`, `set`, `tasks`, `workflow`, `project`\n- **Daemon required**: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `loop`, `shutdown`\n\n**Key Flag Parsing**:\n- Supports `--help`, `-h` at any level\n- Commands parse flags manually (no flag package used)\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` env vars for context operations\n\n**Notable Features**:\n- Live log streaming with `-f` (follow) flag via gRPC metadata `x-cloche-follow`\n- Bare positional arg support (e.g., `cloche run develop` without `--workflow`)\n- HTTP tasks endpoint via `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var (default `localhost:8080`)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Daemon Setup (cloched/main.go)**\n\n**Initialization Flow**:\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config` (TOML format)\n2. Init SQLite store (WAL mode, busy timeout 5s, single connection)\n3. Mark stale runs as failed on startup\n4. Init container runtime (Docker or local)\n5. Create gRPC server and HTTP server (if `CLOCHE_HTTP` set)\n6. Set up evolution trigger (if configured)\n7. Auto-run active projects' host workflows\n\n**gRPC Server**:\n- Listens on `CLOCHE_LISTEN` or default `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`\n- Registered service: `pb.RegisterClocheServiceServer(grpcServer, srv)`\n- Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n**Container Runtime Options**:\n- **Docker** (default): `internal/adapters/docker`\n- **Local**: Runs agent directly (no container), uses `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH`\n\n**Key Helpers**:\n- `envOrConfig()`: Priority is env > config file > fallback default\n- `listen()`: Parses `unix://` socket paths or TCP addresses\n- `autoRunActiveProjects()`: Runs host workflows for active projects\n\n---\n\n### 4. **In-Container Agent (cloche-agent/main.go)**\n\n**Simple Entry Point**:\n- Takes workflow file path as first arg: `cloche-agent .cloche/develop.cloche`\n- Reads `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` env var and unsets it (security)\n- Uses `internal/agent.Runner` to execute workflow\n- Outputs JSON-line status messages to stdout\n\n**Status Output**:\n- Messages are parsed by daemon in `grpc/server.go` `trackRun()` method\n- Types: `MsgStepStarted`, `MsgStepCompleted`, `MsgRunCompleted`, `MsgLog`, `MsgRunTitle`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **gRPC Proto Files and Service Definition**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n**Service**: `ClocheService` with 10 RPCs:\n- `RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) -> RunWorkflowResponse`\n- `GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) -> GetStatusResponse`\n- `StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) -> stream LogEntry`\n- `StopRun(StopRunRequest) -> StopRunResponse`\n- `ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) -> ListRunsResponse`\n- `Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) -> ShutdownResponse`\n- `DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) -> DeleteContainerResponse`\n- `EnableLoop(EnableLoopRequest) -> EnableLoopResponse`\n- `DisableLoop(DisableLoopRequest) -> DisableLoopResponse`\n- `GetProjectInfo(GetProjectInfoRequest) -> GetProjectInfoResponse`\n\n**Key Message Types**:\n- `RunWorkflowRequest`: `workflow_name`, `project_dir`, `image`, `prompt`, `keep_container`, `title`\n- `GetStatusResponse`: `run_id`, `workflow_name`, `state`, `current_step`, `step_executions`, `container_id`, `is_host`, `title`\n- `LogEntry`: `type`, `step_name`, `result`, `message`, `timestamp`\n- `ListRunsRequest`: `all`, `project_dir`, `state`, `limit`, `task_id`\n- `RunSummary`: `run_id`, `workflow_name`, `state`, `container_id`, `title`, `is_host`, `project_dir`\n\n**Generated Code**: `api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go` (protoc-gen-go-grpc v1.6.1)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Daemon Client Connection** (from cloche/main.go)\n\n```go\n// Lines 105-117 of cmd/cloche/main.go\naddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\nif addr == \"\" {\n    addr = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\n}\n\nconn, err := grpc.NewClient(addr, grpc.WithTransportCredentials(insecure.NewCredentials()))\nif err != nil {\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"failed to connect: %v\\n\", err)\n    os.Exit(1)\n}\ndefer conn.Close()\n\nclient := pb.NewClocheServiceClient(conn)\nctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\ndefer cancel()\n```\n\n**Client Usage Pattern**:\n- All daemon commands call `client.RunWorkflow()`, `client.GetStatus()`, etc.\n- Streaming calls (logs) use background context for follow mode\n- Metadata passed via `metadata.NewOutgoingContext()` for follow flag\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Version-Related Code**\n\n**Version Handling**:\n- `.cloche/version` file exists (created by `cloche init` with content `\"1\\n\"`)\n- No runtime version checking in daemon or CLI\n- Acts as a schema marker for project initialization\n\n**Version File Creation** (`cmd/cloche/init.go`):\n```\n{filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"version\"), versionContent, 0644}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Module and Dependencies** (go.mod)\n\n```\nmodule github.com/cloche-dev/cloche\ngo 1.25.3\n\nrequire:\n- google.golang.org/grpc v1.79.1\n- google.golang.org/protobuf v1.36.11\n- modernc.org/sqlite v1.46.1\n- github.com/BurntSushi/toml v1.6.0\n- github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Docker Container Operations** (internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go)\n\n**Container Lifecycle**:\n\n1. **Start** (`Start()` method):\n   - Creates container with `docker create`\n   - Copies project files to `/workspace/` with `docker cp`\n   - Copies `.cloche/overrides/` on top of workspace\n   - Copies Claude auth files (`~/.claude`, `~/.claude.json`)\n   - Runs wrapping command as root, then `su agent` for security\n   - Starts container with `docker start`\n\n2. **Management Operations**:\n   - `Stop()`: `docker stop <container>`\n   - `Wait()`: `docker wait <container>` (returns exit code)\n   - `Logs()`: `docker logs <container>`\n   - `AttachOutput()`: `docker logs -f` with pipe\n   - `CopyFrom()`: `docker cp <container>:/path /dst`\n   - `Inspect()`: `docker inspect --format` (checks running state, exit code)\n   - `Remove()`: `docker rm -f <container>`\n\n**Environment Passing**:\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`: Run ID set automatically\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`: Passed if set in host environment\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`: Comma-separated `KEY=VALUE` pairs from env var\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS`: Comma-separated `host:container` volume mounts\n\n**Image Ensurance** (`ImageEnsurer` interface):\n- Automatic image rebuild if project Dockerfile changed\n- Implemented in Docker adapter, builds with `docker build`\n\n**Default Container Setup**:\n- User: `root` initially, then `su agent` for workflow execution\n- Workdir: `/workspace`\n- Host entry: `--add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway`\n- Command wrapper: Chowns workspace, cleans up plugins, execs agent\n\n---\n\n### 10. **gRPC Server Implementation** (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)\n\n**Type**: `ClocheServer struct`\n- Fields: `store`, `captures`, `logStore`, `container`, `defaultImage`, `evolution`, `logBroadcast`, `shutdownFn`\n- Maps: `runIDs` (run_id -> container_id), `loops` (project_dir -> orchestration loop)\n\n**Key Methods**:\n\n- **RunWorkflow**: \n  - Generates unique run ID (retries on collision)\n  - Writes prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n  - Creates run in store\n  - Launches container in background goroutine\n  - Returns immediately\n\n- **trackRun**:\n  - Parses JSON-line status messages from agent output\n  - Updates run state in store\n  - Broadcasts logs via publisher\n  - Extracts results to git branch\n  - Handles container retention policy\n  - Fires evolution trigger\n\n- **StreamLogs**:\n  - Checks for follow mode via gRPC metadata `x-cloche-follow`\n  - Serves from `full.log` or capture-based streaming\n  - Supports filtering by step name and log type\n  - For active runs + follow: sends existing logs then tails live\n\n- **GetStatus**: Loads run, checks container liveness, returns step executions\n\n- **ListRuns**: Filters by project/state/limit, returns summaries\n\n- **EnableLoop/DisableLoop**: Manages orchestration loops (three-phase or legacy)\n\n- **DeleteContainer**: Removes by run ID or container ID\n\n---\n\n### 11. **SQLite Store** (internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go)\n\n**Schema**:\n- `runs`: id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id, task_id\n- `step_executions`: run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n- `log_files`: run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at\n- `merge_queue`: run_id, branch, project, status, enqueued_at, completed_at\n- `evolution_log`: id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, created_at, classification, changes_json, knowledge_delta\n\n**Features**:\n- WAL mode for concurrent reads\n- Busy timeout: 5 seconds\n- Single open connection (serialized writes)\n- Idempotent migrations (ALTER TABLE)\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Ports (Interfaces)**\n\n**internal/ports/container.go**:\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n    EnsureImage(ctx, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n**internal/ports/store.go**:\n```go\ntype RunStore interface { /* 8 methods */ }\ntype CaptureStore interface { /* 2 methods */ }\ntype LogStore interface { /* 4 methods */ }\ntype EvolutionStore interface { /* 3 methods */ }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Configuration System**\n\n**Config Sources** (internal/config/config.go):\n\n1. **Global Config**: `~/.config/cloche/config` (TOML, per-machine daemon defaults)\n2. **Project Config**: `.cloche/config.toml` (TOML, per-project settings)\n\n**Config Sections**:\n- `[daemon]`: listen, http, image, db, runtime, agent_path, llm_command\n- `[evolution]`: enabled, debounce_seconds, min_confidence, max_prompt_bullets\n- `[orchestration]`: concurrency, stagger_seconds, list_tasks_command, dedup_seconds\n\n**Defaults**:\n- evolution.enabled: true\n- evolution.debounce_seconds: 30\n- evolution.min_confidence: \"medium\"\n- orchestration.concurrency: 1\n- orchestration.stagger_seconds: 1.0\n\n---\n\n### 14. **Domain Types**\n\n**RunState** (internal/domain/run.go):\n```go\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n**Run Struct**:\n- ID, WorkflowName, State, ActiveSteps, StepExecutions\n- StartedAt, CompletedAt, ProjectDir, ErrorMessage\n- ContainerID, BaseSHA (for git branch creation)\n- ContainerKept, Title, IsHost, ParentRunID, TaskID\n\n**RunID Generation** (internal/domain/namegen.go):\n- Format: `<workflow>-<adjective>-<noun>-<hex>`\n- Example: `develop-vivid-tide-3c0b`\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive exploration covers all the critical architectural components, CLI setup, gRPC infrastructure, container orchestration, and data persistence mechanisms of the Cloche system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af7af0dde55a5556b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 73554\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 66961</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a8a233a-9bc4-4d5b-81f2-86c5b6995110","uuid":"a664a70d-1b4c-4c91-a5b7-b488ded82de7","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The overall directory structure (cmd/, internal/, etc.)\n2. The existing CLI setup for cloche, cloched, and cloche-agent (main.go files, how flags are parsed)\n3. The existing gRPC proto files and service definitions\n4. How the daemon client connects (gRPC client setup)\n5. Any existing version-related code\n6. The go.mod file for module name and dependencies\n7. How Docker/container operations are done (for running docker commands)\n\nBe very thorough - read the key files in full.","agentId":"af7af0dde55a5556b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me create a detailed summary.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Go Project Architecture and Implementation\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the Cloche project. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n### 1. **Overall Directory Structure**\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── cmd/                          # Three binary entry points\n│   ├── cloche/                   # CLI client (short-lived)\n│   ├── cloched/                  # Daemon (long-running)\n│   └── cloche-agent/             # In-container agent\n├── internal/                      # Core domain logic\n│   ├── domain/                   # Types: Run, Workflow, RunState\n│   ├── ports/                    # Interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore)\n│   ├── adapters/                 # Implementations\n│   │   ├── docker/               # Docker runtime + image building/extraction\n│   │   ├── sqlite/               # SQLite store (runs, captures, logs, evolution)\n│   │   ├── grpc/                 # gRPC server\n│   │   ├── local/                # Local (non-container) runtime\n│   │   ├── web/                  # HTTP web dashboard\n│   │   └── agents/               # Agent adapters (prompt, generic)\n│   ├── config/                   # Configuration (TOML from ~/.config/cloche and .cloche/)\n│   ├── dsl/                      # Workflow DSL parser/lexer\n│   ├── agent/                    # Container-side agent runner\n│   ├── host/                     # Host workflow executor\n│   ├── evolution/                # Self-evolving tooling\n│   ├── logstream/                # Log broadcasting\n│   ├── protocol/                 # Status message types\n│   ├── runcontext/               # Context variables\n│   └── engine/                   # Execution engine\n├── api/                           # Protocol Buffers definitions\n│   ├── proto/cloche/v1/          # cloche.proto\n│   └── clochepb/                 # Generated gRPC code\n├── examples/                      # Example projects\n├── docker/                        # Docker image build artifacts\n├── docs/                          # User documentation\n├── test/                          # Integration tests\n├── go.mod / go.sum               # Module: github.com/cloche-dev/cloche\n└── Makefile                       # Build automation\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **CLI Setup (cloche/main.go)**\n\n**Module**: `github.com/cloche-dev/cloche`\n\n**gRPC Client Connection**:\n- Address: Env var `CLOCHE_ADDR` or default `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`\n- Credentials: Insecure (no TLS)\n- Timeout: 30 seconds for most operations\n- Connection: `grpc.NewClient()` with `insecure.NewCredentials()`\n\n**Commands (Daemon-Aware)**:\n- **No daemon needed**: `init`, `health`, `get`, `set`, `tasks`, `workflow`, `project`\n- **Daemon required**: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `loop`, `shutdown`\n\n**Key Flag Parsing**:\n- Supports `--help`, `-h` at any level\n- Commands parse flags manually (no flag package used)\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` env vars for context operations\n\n**Notable Features**:\n- Live log streaming with `-f` (follow) flag via gRPC metadata `x-cloche-follow`\n- Bare positional arg support (e.g., `cloche run develop` without `--workflow`)\n- HTTP tasks endpoint via `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var (default `localhost:8080`)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Daemon Setup (cloched/main.go)**\n\n**Initialization Flow**:\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config` (TOML format)\n2. Init SQLite store (WAL mode, busy timeout 5s, single connection)\n3. Mark stale runs as failed on startup\n4. Init container runtime (Docker or local)\n5. Create gRPC server and HTTP server (if `CLOCHE_HTTP` set)\n6. Set up evolution trigger (if configured)\n7. Auto-run active projects' host workflows\n\n**gRPC Server**:\n- Listens on `CLOCHE_LISTEN` or default `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`\n- Registered service: `pb.RegisterClocheServiceServer(grpcServer, srv)`\n- Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n**Container Runtime Options**:\n- **Docker** (default): `internal/adapters/docker`\n- **Local**: Runs agent directly (no container), uses `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH`\n\n**Key Helpers**:\n- `envOrConfig()`: Priority is env > config file > fallback default\n- `listen()`: Parses `unix://` socket paths or TCP addresses\n- `autoRunActiveProjects()`: Runs host workflows for active projects\n\n---\n\n### 4. **In-Container Agent (cloche-agent/main.go)**\n\n**Simple Entry Point**:\n- Takes workflow file path as first arg: `cloche-agent .cloche/develop.cloche`\n- Reads `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` env var and unsets it (security)\n- Uses `internal/agent.Runner` to execute workflow\n- Outputs JSON-line status messages to stdout\n\n**Status Output**:\n- Messages are parsed by daemon in `grpc/server.go` `trackRun()` method\n- Types: `MsgStepStarted`, `MsgStepCompleted`, `MsgRunCompleted`, `MsgLog`, `MsgRunTitle`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **gRPC Proto Files and Service Definition**\n\n**File**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n**Service**: `ClocheService` with 10 RPCs:\n- `RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) -> RunWorkflowResponse`\n- `GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) -> GetStatusResponse`\n- `StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) -> stream LogEntry`\n- `StopRun(StopRunRequest) -> StopRunResponse`\n- `ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) -> ListRunsResponse`\n- `Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) -> ShutdownResponse`\n- `DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) -> DeleteContainerResponse`\n- `EnableLoop(EnableLoopRequest) -> EnableLoopResponse`\n- `DisableLoop(DisableLoopRequest) -> DisableLoopResponse`\n- `GetProjectInfo(GetProjectInfoRequest) -> GetProjectInfoResponse`\n\n**Key Message Types**:\n- `RunWorkflowRequest`: `workflow_name`, `project_dir`, `image`, `prompt`, `keep_container`, `title`\n- `GetStatusResponse`: `run_id`, `workflow_name`, `state`, `current_step`, `step_executions`, `container_id`, `is_host`, `title`\n- `LogEntry`: `type`, `step_name`, `result`, `message`, `timestamp`\n- `ListRunsRequest`: `all`, `project_dir`, `state`, `limit`, `task_id`\n- `RunSummary`: `run_id`, `workflow_name`, `state`, `container_id`, `title`, `is_host`, `project_dir`\n\n**Generated Code**: `api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go` (protoc-gen-go-grpc v1.6.1)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Daemon Client Connection** (from cloche/main.go)\n\n```go\n// Lines 105-117 of cmd/cloche/main.go\naddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\nif addr == \"\" {\n    addr = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\n}\n\nconn, err := grpc.NewClient(addr, grpc.WithTransportCredentials(insecure.NewCredentials()))\nif err != nil {\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"failed to connect: %v\\n\", err)\n    os.Exit(1)\n}\ndefer conn.Close()\n\nclient := pb.NewClocheServiceClient(conn)\nctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\ndefer cancel()\n```\n\n**Client Usage Pattern**:\n- All daemon commands call `client.RunWorkflow()`, `client.GetStatus()`, etc.\n- Streaming calls (logs) use background context for follow mode\n- Metadata passed via `metadata.NewOutgoingContext()` for follow flag\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Version-Related Code**\n\n**Version Handling**:\n- `.cloche/version` file exists (created by `cloche init` with content `\"1\\n\"`)\n- No runtime version checking in daemon or CLI\n- Acts as a schema marker for project initialization\n\n**Version File Creation** (`cmd/cloche/init.go`):\n```\n{filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"version\"), versionContent, 0644}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Module and Dependencies** (go.mod)\n\n```\nmodule github.com/cloche-dev/cloche\ngo 1.25.3\n\nrequire:\n- google.golang.org/grpc v1.79.1\n- google.golang.org/protobuf v1.36.11\n- modernc.org/sqlite v1.46.1\n- github.com/BurntSushi/toml v1.6.0\n- github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Docker Container Operations** (internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go)\n\n**Container Lifecycle**:\n\n1. **Start** (`Start()` method):\n   - Creates container with `docker create`\n   - Copies project files to `/workspace/` with `docker cp`\n   - Copies `.cloche/overrides/` on top of workspace\n   - Copies Claude auth files (`~/.claude`, `~/.claude.json`)\n   - Runs wrapping command as root, then `su agent` for security\n   - Starts container with `docker start`\n\n2. **Management Operations**:\n   - `Stop()`: `docker stop <container>`\n   - `Wait()`: `docker wait <container>` (returns exit code)\n   - `Logs()`: `docker logs <container>`\n   - `AttachOutput()`: `docker logs -f` with pipe\n   - `CopyFrom()`: `docker cp <container>:/path /dst`\n   - `Inspect()`: `docker inspect --format` (checks running state, exit code)\n   - `Remove()`: `docker rm -f <container>`\n\n**Environment Passing**:\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`: Run ID set automatically\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`: Passed if set in host environment\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`: Comma-separated `KEY=VALUE` pairs from env var\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS`: Comma-separated `host:container` volume mounts\n\n**Image Ensurance** (`ImageEnsurer` interface):\n- Automatic image rebuild if project Dockerfile changed\n- Implemented in Docker adapter, builds with `docker build`\n\n**Default Container Setup**:\n- User: `root` initially, then `su agent` for workflow execution\n- Workdir: `/workspace`\n- Host entry: `--add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway`\n- Command wrapper: Chowns workspace, cleans up plugins, execs agent\n\n---\n\n### 10. **gRPC Server Implementation** (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)\n\n**Type**: `ClocheServer struct`\n- Fields: `store`, `captures`, `logStore`, `container`, `defaultImage`, `evolution`, `logBroadcast`, `shutdownFn`\n- Maps: `runIDs` (run_id -> container_id), `loops` (project_dir -> orchestration loop)\n\n**Key Methods**:\n\n- **RunWorkflow**: \n  - Generates unique run ID (retries on collision)\n  - Writes prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n  - Creates run in store\n  - Launches container in background goroutine\n  - Returns immediately\n\n- **trackRun**:\n  - Parses JSON-line status messages from agent output\n  - Updates run state in store\n  - Broadcasts logs via publisher\n  - Extracts results to git branch\n  - Handles container retention policy\n  - Fires evolution trigger\n\n- **StreamLogs**:\n  - Checks for follow mode via gRPC metadata `x-cloche-follow`\n  - Serves from `full.log` or capture-based streaming\n  - Supports filtering by step name and log type\n  - For active runs + follow: sends existing logs then tails live\n\n- **GetStatus**: Loads run, checks container liveness, returns step executions\n\n- **ListRuns**: Filters by project/state/limit, returns summaries\n\n- **EnableLoop/DisableLoop**: Manages orchestration loops (three-phase or legacy)\n\n- **DeleteContainer**: Removes by run ID or container ID\n\n---\n\n### 11. **SQLite Store** (internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go)\n\n**Schema**:\n- `runs`: id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id, task_id\n- `step_executions`: run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, prompt_text, agent_output, attempt_number\n- `log_files`: run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at\n- `merge_queue`: run_id, branch, project, status, enqueued_at, completed_at\n- `evolution_log`: id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, created_at, classification, changes_json, knowledge_delta\n\n**Features**:\n- WAL mode for concurrent reads\n- Busy timeout: 5 seconds\n- Single open connection (serialized writes)\n- Idempotent migrations (ALTER TABLE)\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Ports (Interfaces)**\n\n**internal/ports/container.go**:\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n    EnsureImage(ctx, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n**internal/ports/store.go**:\n```go\ntype RunStore interface { /* 8 methods */ }\ntype CaptureStore interface { /* 2 methods */ }\ntype LogStore interface { /* 4 methods */ }\ntype EvolutionStore interface { /* 3 methods */ }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Configuration System**\n\n**Config Sources** (internal/config/config.go):\n\n1. **Global Config**: `~/.config/cloche/config` (TOML, per-machine daemon defaults)\n2. **Project Config**: `.cloche/config.toml` (TOML, per-project settings)\n\n**Config Sections**:\n- `[daemon]`: listen, http, image, db, runtime, agent_path, llm_command\n- `[evolution]`: enabled, debounce_seconds, min_confidence, max_prompt_bullets\n- `[orchestration]`: concurrency, stagger_seconds, list_tasks_command, dedup_seconds\n\n**Defaults**:\n- evolution.enabled: true\n- evolution.debounce_seconds: 30\n- evolution.min_confidence: \"medium\"\n- orchestration.concurrency: 1\n- orchestration.stagger_seconds: 1.0\n\n---\n\n### 14. **Domain Types**\n\n**RunState** (internal/domain/run.go):\n```go\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n**Run Struct**:\n- ID, WorkflowName, State, ActiveSteps, StepExecutions\n- StartedAt, CompletedAt, ProjectDir, ErrorMessage\n- ContainerID, BaseSHA (for git branch creation)\n- ContainerKept, Title, IsHost, ParentRunID, TaskID\n\n**RunID Generation** (internal/domain/namegen.go):\n- Format: `<workflow>-<adjective>-<noun>-<hex>`\n- Example: `develop-vivid-tide-3c0b`\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive exploration covers all the critical architectural components, CLI setup, gRPC infrastructure, container orchestration, and data persistence mechanisms of the Cloche system."}],"totalDurationMs":66961,"totalTokens":73554,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2076,"cache_read_input_tokens":67239,"output_tokens":4239,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2076},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
