l\n  }\n  ```\n- Full method name: `/cloche.v1.ClocheService/GetVersion`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Version Module Tests\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/version/version_test.go`\n\n**Tests:**\n1. `TestVersion()`: Verifies version string is not empty and equals \"0.1.0\"\n2. `TestVersionNoTrailingNewline()`: Verifies trailing whitespace is properly stripped\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Binary | Flags | Entry Point | Output Format | Dependencies |\n|--------|-------|-------------|--------------|--------------|\n| `cloche` | `-v, --version` | cmdVersion() | 3-line multi-version output | gRPC daemon, Docker |\n| `cloched` | `-v, --version` | main() direct | Single-line daemon version | None |\n| `cloche-agent` | `-v, --version` | main() direct | Single-line agent version | None |\n\n### Key Design Points\n\n1. **All three binaries share the same version file** (`internal/version/VERSION`)\n2. **CLI performs cross-service version discovery**, warning on mismatches\n3. **Daemon and Agent are simple and stateless** regarding version reporting\n4. **gRPC endpoint enables programmatic version checking** independent of daemon command-line\n5. **Embedded VERSION file** ensures version is baked into each binary at compile time\n6. **3-second timeout** on gRPC calls prevents CLI hang if daemon is unresponsive"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa2ae32e1519e37cb (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54274\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 23830</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5888bf68-422b-4315-97ee-07c9cf3aacfd","uuid":"edd995cb-e045-4e36-9158-1248c7f86769","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the version reporting implementation in this codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read internal/version/ directory - all files\n2. Read cmd/cloche/main.go - how does the CLI handle -v/--version?\n3. Read cmd/cloched/main.go - how does the daemon handle -v/--version?\n4. Read cmd/cloche-agent/main.go - how d