`cloched` (Daemon): long-running, manages Docker containers, records captures, exposes gRPC API\n  - `cloche-agent` (In-Container): autonomous, parses DSL, executes steps, streams status\n- **Communication protocols:**\n  - CLI ↔ Daemon: gRPC with protobuf contracts\n  - Agent ↔ Daemon: structured JSON over stdout\n- **Workflow DSL vocabulary** (workflow, step, result, wiring, done, abort)\n- **Hexagonal architecture** (ports and adapters)\n- **Container model** (one container per run, git-based file extraction)\n- **Capture system** (step inputs/outputs/results recorded)\n- **Security boundaries** (filesystem, network, environment isolation)\n\n#### 4. **docs/workflows.md** (`/workspace/docs/workflows.md`)\nComplete workflow DSL reference with:\n- **Workflow locations:**\n  - Container workflows (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) — run in Docker\n  - Host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — run on host machine\n  - Three workflow phases: `list-tasks`, `main`, `finalize`\n- **Step types:** `agent` (prompt), `script` (run), `workflow` (dispatch container workflow, host only)\n- **DSL syntax** (workflow declaration, step config, wiring, results)\n- **Wire output mappings** (extract values from step output, inject as env vars)\n- **Key properties** (type inference, result declaration, separate wiring, parse-time validation)\n- **Execution model** (container vs host, environment variables)\n- **`list-tasks` output format** (JSONL with id, status, title, description, metadata)\n- **Host workflow example** (three-phase orchestration)\n\n#### 5. **docs/USAGE.md** (`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`)\nComplete CLI usage guide with:\n- **Core concepts** (workflow, step, result, wiring, terminals)\n- **Workflow DSL detailed reference** (step configuration, container blocks, host blocks, wiring syntax)\n- **Step configuration keys:**\n  - `prompt`, `run`, `workflow_name`\n  - `results`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`\n  - `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `feedback`, `prompt_step`\n- *